{"key":"processedPost-14504843","value":{"id":14504843,"first":14504513,"last":14505051,"when":1306269285,"utime":"05/24/11 11:34 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>2jew4u said:</strong><br />Prolly the same- Think that they dont really use the light except for triggers, and a direction to grow-</blockquote><br />That is flat out wrong.&nbsp; What triggers?&nbsp; Cubensis and many other mushrooms will pin in darkness.&nbsp; Also, they'll grow straight up in total darkness, so they don't use light for direction to grow either.&nbsp; Mushrooms are using light as an energy source and orient caps towards it to gain maximum benefit.<br />To the OP, hopefully those 40 and 60 watt lamps are fluorescent in the 5000K to 7000K range.&nbsp; If so, a single 13 or 26 watt CFL lamp will be plenty if it's six inches or so from your terrarium.<br />RR"}}